Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 981 "Welcome \Nto Bocchan Restaurant (Part One)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.04,0:00:08.00,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshida-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.38,0:00:17.41,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.91,0:00:24.68,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It's really hurt. Did it get hit by a car?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.68,0:00:27.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, it doesn't seem like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.80,0:00:31.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any signs \Nthat it was hit by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.11,0:00:35.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone probably hit or kicked it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.66,0:00:37.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would someone do something so cruel?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.94,0:00:39.27,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.80,0:00:43.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This might serve as a clue \Nto finding the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.23,0:00:44.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,These bloodstains and fibers...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.94,0:00:47.76,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,The cat must've scratched something \Nthe culprit was wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.76,0:00:51.69,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yellow and pink... \NThat's distinctive clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.09,0:00:54.21,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,We need to find the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.60,0:00:59.08,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,but we also need to get \Nthis cat to a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.08,0:01:00.33,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshida-san, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.33,0:01:01.18,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.76,0:01:04.53,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's oddly kind to animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.59,0:01:09.84,DCMain,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,He's in a weakened state, but he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.19,0:01:13.35,DCMain,DOCTOR,0000,0000,0000,,It'll take some time, but he'll get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.34,0:01:20.35,Hospital,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Beika City Animal Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.03,0:01:19.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, how will we find the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.74,0:01:23.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a case?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.85,0:01:27.85,Bocchan,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan Restaurant
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.01,0:01:30.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan Restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.26,0:01:32.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You kids again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.09,0:01:35.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are we cursed in some way?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.11,0:01:37.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right back at you...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.25,0:01:51.10,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That man's shirt is yellow and pink!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.10,0:01:52.75,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.10,0:01:54.64,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,The animal abuser.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.52,0:01:59.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does this have something to do with that cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.97,0:02:06.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The rhythm on my lips is footloose!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.54,0:02:08.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The rhythm of my detective \Nskills is perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:10.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,An odd restaurant with characters \Nplucked from a novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.16,0:02:12.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys take \Non a serial murder case!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.37,0:02:13.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.91,0:02:15.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.74,0:02:17.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:04:02.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)}Welcome to Bocchan Restaurant \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.68,0:03:59.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Welcome to Bocchan Restaurant, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.40,0:04:07.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The victim was Bocchan Restaurant employee \NKoga Ushio-san, thirty-six years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.80,0:04:07.64,Ushio,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Koga Ushio (36) \NBocchan Restaurant Head Receptionist
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.98,0:04:12.64,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The weapon hasn't been found, but is \Nmost likely a kitchen knife-like blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.64,0:04:22.65,Lake,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Sanshiro Lake
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.92,0:04:15.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The body was abandoned in Sanshiro Lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.72,0:04:21.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the body's condition, he \Nwas killed last night around midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.91,0:04:25.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You lot again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.94,0:04:29.15,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to get in our way by \Nwalking around the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.15,0:04:30.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:32.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Continue, Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.43,0:04:33.51,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.51,0:04:38.21,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This morning, Bocchan Restaurant \Nmanager Akazawa Zenichi-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.21,0:04:41.63,Zenichi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Akazawa Zenichi (60) \NBocchan Restaurant Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.35,0:04:41.68,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}whose home is located here at the \Nrestaurant, discovered the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:43.80,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Who could have killed Uranari?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.06,0:04:49.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that cat happened to be \Nhere at the crime scene last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:50.72,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:54.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since their crime had been witnessed, \Nthey intended to silence him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.94,0:04:57.74,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they hurt the kitty?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.74,0:04:58.98,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,How awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.17,0:05:01.62,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a cat that witnessed their crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.62,0:05:04.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's plausible given a criminal's mentality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.46,0:05:09.05,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Then we should find the culprit \Nfor that cat's sake, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.05,0:05:09.87,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.87,0:05:11.18,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.18,0:05:11.87,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.09,0:05:17.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the criminal profile, since the murder \Noccurred within the restaurant late at night,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.72,0:05:20.63,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,it's hard to imagine that it \Nwas committed by an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:25.13,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,So it's likely that the murder was committed \Nby someone who works at Bocchan Restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.48,0:05:28.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is probably someone \Nwho works at the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:29.28,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.75,0:05:31.85,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,All the employees have arrived for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:33.84,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.84,0:05:34.64,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.17,0:05:51.83,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's our uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:55.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.37,0:05:58.29,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Boys, Uranari's been killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:05:59.15,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.15,0:06:00.17,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.33,0:06:03.75,Rokusuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Bocchan \NShima Rokusuke (22)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.60,0:06:02.90,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What evildoer could do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.90,0:06:06.42,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The sun may forgive them, but I will not!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.59,0:06:10.05,Uni,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kiyo \NKiyohara Uni (71)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.61,0:06:07.91,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}How marvelous.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.91,0:06:12.18,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Bocchan's sense of justice is \Nthis old Kiyo's pride and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.34,0:06:14.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan? Kiyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.06,0:06:17.98,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now you've done it, you dastardly Red Shirt!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.10,0:06:18.14,Izumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Yama Arashi \NHotta Izumi (32)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.15,0:06:20.27,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,All to get at Madonna!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.44,0:06:23.36,Chiaki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Madonna \NToyama Chiaki (24)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.75,0:06:23.17,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Please, Yama Arashi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.37,0:06:26.03,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,You make it seem like \NI'm the reason for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.55,0:06:30.78,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never do anything as \Nsenseless as kill someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:31.53,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.97,0:06:33.54,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:36.29,Kozo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Nodaiko \NYoshikawa Kozo (43)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.54,0:06:36.29,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You suspect the president? What a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:38.08,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Nodaiko, stay out of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.44,0:06:39.79,DCMain,TANUKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.37,0:06:42.46,Toyoo,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Tanuki \NTanuma Toyoo (58)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.79,0:06:42.46,DCMain,TANUKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let's not cast suspicion upon each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:45.21,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're always afraid to \Nrock the boat, Tanuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:51.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan Restaurant recreates the \Nworld inside a novel, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.42,0:06:53.46,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed you noticed, son!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:54.97,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,That's our selling point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.97,0:06:57.86,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What? A novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.86,0:07:00.48,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't heard of "Bocchan"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.97,0:07:03.24,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they are first graders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.24,0:07:04.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.43,0:07:06.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko, could you explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.03,0:07:14.49,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Bocchan" is a famous novel written \Nduring the Meiji Era by Natsume Soseki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.07,0:07:19.50,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The protagonist Bocchan leaves \Nhis old maidservant Kiyo-san in Tokyo
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.83,0:07:23.31,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,to begin teaching at a school in Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.74,0:07:26.02,DCItalic,MAN 1,0000,0000,0000,,Grasshoppers? These are locusts!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.02,0:07:28.13,DCItalic,MAN 2,0000,0000,0000,,Grasshoppers and locusts are the same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.56,0:07:34.01,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But his students pull pranks on him, \Nlike putting grasshoppers in his bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.66,0:07:37.51,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The principal Tanuki is irresponsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.66,0:07:42.27,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, he learns that his colleague \NUranari-kun's fiancée, Madonna-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.27,0:07:45.39,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,has been taken from him \Nby head teacher Red Shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.39,0:07:48.78,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The righteous Bocchan is \Nunable to forgive them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.78,0:07:52.17,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,so he and his colleague Yama \NArashi-san beat up Red Shirt
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.17,0:07:54.78,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,and his obsequious sidekick Nodaiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.35,0:07:57.66,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a very satisfying story!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.79,0:08:00.33,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.33,0:08:01.54,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:03.78,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.78,0:08:08.23,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You get to wear those pretty clothes \Nwhile bringing customers their food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.23,0:08:10.67,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not my only job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.94,0:08:13.09,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You do other stuff, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.62,0:08:22.85,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan Dancers?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:24.90,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,They all dance together...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:33.61,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,We should get started on \Nlooking for the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.61,0:08:34.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.95,0:08:37.42,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is probably one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:43.35,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're temporarily closed, \Nthey could let us leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.35,0:08:47.33,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,The police insist we stay \Nso they can question us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:50.84,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But they'll be providing food, \Nso we won't have to buy our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.06,0:08:53.84,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have any ambition?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.46,0:08:58.11,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,I do appreciate not having \Nto buy my own lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.57,0:09:03.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those three...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.33,0:09:05.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Their colleague was just murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.76,0:09:08.23,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,It's understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.21,0:09:12.57,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the victim Uranari-san was—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.15,0:09:16.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did he have problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:22.54,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You think I did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.89,0:09:26.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We received testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.39,0:09:31.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You and the victim Uranari-san, or \NKoga Ushio, were romantic rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.37,0:09:35.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You fought over Toyama \NChiaki-san, who plays Madonna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:36.05,DCMain,AKAZAKA,0000,0000,0000,,That's—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.05,0:09:37.16,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:41.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And you live on restaurant grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.55,0:09:46.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible you invited over your \Nromantic rival last night, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.39,0:09:48.70,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.70,0:09:52.57,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,He was responsible for all \Nof our reception staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.57,0:09:56.86,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of manager would murder \Nthe backbone of his business?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.13,0:09:59.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,One thing may have led to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.52,0:10:03.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You invited Uranari-san over and \Nasked him to leave Madonna-san alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.47,0:10:05.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But he wouldn't listen, so without \Nthinking, you stabbed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.19,0:10:09.63,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I have been holding a knife then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.85,0:10:11.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,To threaten him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.27,0:10:14.63,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Red Shirt is a dastardly fellow \Nwho will do anything to get his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.89,0:10:17.88,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't confuse the novel with reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.27,0:10:21.44,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,If you think I did it, I'd \Nlike to see some evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.19,0:10:27.43,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.93,0:10:30.58,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,Did they both harbor \Nromantic feelings for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.58,0:10:32.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.95,0:10:36.07,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they were simply pretending
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.07,0:10:38.94,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,in front of our customers as \Npart of our business strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:49.96,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It must be shocking to learn that \Ntwo men were fighting over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.14,0:10:55.03,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but if a murder \Nwas committed because of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.03,0:10:56.63,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That would be hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.89,0:11:00.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, what was \Nshe about to say earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.49,0:11:02.70,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Something about Uranari-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.70,0:11:03.62,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.39,0:11:09.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The victim Uranari had a terrible reputation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:12.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you're not mistaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.25,0:11:14.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Uranari is a kind-hearted and good man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.98,0:11:16.40,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,In the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.60,0:11:21.91,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But apparently they're all totally \Ndifferent from the characters they play.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.18,0:11:23.66,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.92,0:11:25.66,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,For example, the dastardly Red Shirt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.90,0:11:29.83,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,is a good-natured man who \Ncares for his employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.35,0:11:34.38,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan is actually a twisted \Nman with no sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.80,0:11:37.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yama Arashi is a delicate crybaby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.13,0:11:40.45,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,And Madonna seems plain,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.45,0:11:43.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,but she wrestled as a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.65,0:11:47.82,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Uranari was incredibly strict,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.82,0:11:51.69,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,and he often yelled at his subordinates \Nas the head receptionist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.60,0:11:54.86,DCItalic,URANARI,0000,0000,0000,,Your acting is weak! All of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.35,0:11:57.11,DCItalic,URANARI,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting paid, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.11,0:11:59.30,DCItalic,URANARI,0000,0000,0000,,Perform your roles thoroughly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:00.74,DCItalic,URANARI,0000,0000,0000,,Idiots! Fools! Morons!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:02.54,DCItalic,URANARI,0000,0000,0000,,Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.51,0:12:08.72,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, everyone working in customer \Nservice strongly disliked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.55,0:12:11.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.06,0:12:13.25,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,The thing she almost said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.70,0:12:16.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So they're nothing like their \Ncharacters from the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:21.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, that means the culprit is \None of the good guys from the novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.69,0:12:23.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Either Bocchan or Yama Arashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.73,0:12:26.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Stop thinking about the novel already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.56,0:12:30.36,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,But they did have old scores to settle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.36,0:12:33.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to question \Nthe reception staff, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.89,0:12:38.48,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All right. Summon them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.71,0:12:44.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not just Red Shirt, but Bocchan and Yama \NArashi had motives for murder, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.70,0:12:59.00,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The question is their alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.30,0:13:05.29,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,We're lucky you happened to come \Nstay at my place last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.29,0:13:08.64,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,We're able to confirm each other's alibis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.64,0:13:10.64,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's about your employee...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:13.92,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Now you think my reception staff did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.92,0:13:17.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They have motive as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.35,0:13:19.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.80,0:13:23.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You were able to confirm \Ntheirs, too? Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.12,0:13:29.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't been able to verify \Nlast night's alibis for...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.44,0:13:31.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Shima-san, who plays Bocchan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.73,0:13:33.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hotta-san, who plays Yama Arashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.33,0:13:36.24,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yoshikawa-san, who plays Nodaiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.92,0:13:39.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You three are the only ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:42.62,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,Having an alibi is the bigger miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:45.05,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,It was midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.29,0:13:48.93,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,And we're suspects because \Nof that? Unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.10,0:13:54.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. We'll have to question you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.62,0:13:56.94,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean we can't leave yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.81,0:14:00.27,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We appreciate your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.72,0:14:10.06,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We received testimony that those \Nthree without alibis hated Uranari.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.06,0:14:11.92,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Question everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:14.69,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Whether it's those three or Red Shirt,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.69,0:14:17.30,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,it's possible that someone mentioned \Na desire to kill Uranari.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.30,0:14:18.83,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.83,0:14:20.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.40,0:14:23.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We should split up and help, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.56,0:14:30.18,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You think I hated Uranari-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:32.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was hard on you, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.37,0:14:35.10,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,My wife left me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:38.10,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,She left me with massive amounts of debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.38,0:14:42.27,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to work as hard \Nas I can in order to pay it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.27,0:14:43.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What I'm asking about is—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.93,0:14:45.78,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But that damn Uranari.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.18,0:14:49.03,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He hurled abuse at me for my weak acting!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.26,0:14:51.66,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell does he think I'm playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:14:58.87,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,No adult man wants to play this role!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.91,0:15:02.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He really is nothing like his role.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.88,0:15:05.63,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,My mom croaked last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.63,0:15:08.10,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,She was complaining until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.10,0:15:11.64,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,She said I was trash who could never \Nhold down a job for very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.17,0:15:17.48,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm clinging to this job \Nto get back at my dead mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.48,0:15:18.98,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that damn Uranari!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:21.39,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,He tells us to act, but there \Nare limits to what a man can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.95,0:15:26.75,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I don't care about justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.53,0:15:34.11,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,My mother still sends me encouraging letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.11,0:15:37.41,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,She says if I wish hard enough for \Nsomething, my dreams will come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.64,0:15:41.13,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,So I asked Uranari countless times
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.13,0:15:44.54,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,to let me play Madonna \Ninstead of Yama Arashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.57,0:15:52.03,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,But he never listened!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:56.96,DCMain,TANUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Those three certainly hated Uranari-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.96,0:15:59.03,DCMain,TANUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but I doubt they had the guts to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:00.64,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The guts?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.40,0:16:03.75,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, this sure is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:07.15,DCMain,TANUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Locust tsukudani is our specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.89,0:16:09.70,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,So it's a fish called locust.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.70,0:16:12.27,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fish. They're grasshoppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.27,0:16:13.41,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Grasshoppers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.88,0:16:16.78,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you don't like your \Nrole, you just have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.45,0:16:20.29,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone was scouted for their specific role.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.73,0:16:22.75,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You were scouted, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.34,0:16:25.34,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,Based solely on my appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.30,0:16:31.87,DCMain,KIYO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm nothing like Kiyo-san either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.11,0:16:41.93,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just happy to have a job here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.93,0:16:44.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, everyone would want to play Madonna-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:48.86,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I meant. \NI had a younger sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.58,0:16:51.92,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,She loved the novel "Bocchan."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.92,0:16:55.86,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,When she learned about this restaurant, \Nshe said she wanted to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.16,0:17:01.37,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,But six months ago, she died from an \Nillness called subarachnoid hemorrhaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.60,0:17:09.17,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I could work here in her \Nplace, so I asked them to hire me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.65,0:17:12.75,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,So you carried out your sister's wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.74,0:17:16.62,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe it was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.08,0:17:22.73,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,If me working here caused a murder, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.72,0:17:34.14,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there's no need to keep \Nup the act in front of a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.76,0:17:39.65,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, I knew that \Neveryone hated Uranari-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:46.64,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,But you need people like \Nthat to manage a business.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.37,0:17:52.25,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Because he understood that, \Nhe played the unlikable role.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.57,0:17:56.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So he was an ideal business partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.92,0:18:00.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that you were \Nromantic rivals, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.06,0:18:04.94,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Opening Bocchan Restaurant has \Nbeen my dream since I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.94,0:18:07.99,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I worked really hard to \Ngather enough capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.64,0:18:10.93,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I never experienced love or marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:15.20,DCMain,AKAZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe I developed \Na romantic rivalry at my age.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.99,0:18:32.79,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't find anything conclusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.01,0:18:39.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is the culprit one of \Nthose three or Red Shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.90,0:18:41.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll figure it out tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.33,0:18:46.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, the next day...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:02.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,"I offer my own death as an \Napology to the man I killed."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.32,0:19:05.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, this was found on \Nthe altar in Red Shirt's home!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.79,0:19:10.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably the weapon \Nused in Uranari's murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.72,0:19:15.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,After killing his romantic rival Uranari,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.51,0:19:19.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,he realized he couldn't escape his \Nguilt, so he took his own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.39,0:19:24.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I knew from the start that \Nthe culprit was Red Shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:28.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who started saying it was Bocchan and \NYama Arashi during the investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:31.98,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,So it was Red Shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.24,0:19:34.08,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It must be hard for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.05,0:19:36.54,DCMain,MADONNA,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.86,0:19:43.50,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean she thinks it's because she was \Ntrying to fulfill her sister's wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.92,0:19:45.15,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.04,0:19:48.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he really did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.61,0:19:51.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then why leave the murder \Nweapon on the altar?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.49,0:19:53.43,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he disposed of it initially,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.43,0:19:57.51,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,but once he decided to kill himself, \Nhe left it there by way of apology.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.95,0:20:01.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And why didn't he write his \Nnote on a piece of paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.93,0:20:03.51,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Because their handwriting would give it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.80,0:20:06.79,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Red Shirt's death wasn't a suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.79,0:20:07.43,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.71,0:20:09.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying it's possible that it was faked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.43,0:20:13.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They knocked him out and \Nhanged him by the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:16.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then they fabricated a suicide note
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.80,0:20:19.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and placed the murder weapon on the altar
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:22.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to frame Red Shirt for the \Nmurder of Uranari-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.47,0:20:24.70,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:27.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, then they \Nmust have left some evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.69,0:20:34.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's damp?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.57,0:20:37.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are drops of water on the leaves \Nof the branch beneath it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.77,0:20:40.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,His hair and clothes are wet, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.97,0:20:42.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:44.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He just got out of the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.64,0:20:47.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting in the way of \Nthe adults! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.11,0:20:52.81,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,If Conan-kun is right, then the \Nculprit is one of those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:54.84,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,It could be Yama Arashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.84,0:20:58.24,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,He's big, so he could've carried Red Shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.24,0:21:01.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We still don't know that \Nthe suicide was faked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:07.02,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,If he could speak to us, we could \Nask him who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.02,0:21:09.70,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if he's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:13.86,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad he'll live, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.86,0:21:17.86,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,He was beaten all over, and \Ntwo of his legs were broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.86,0:21:19.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then it couldn't have been possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.23,0:21:20.46,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's impossible?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.51,0:21:25.05,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.61,0:21:27.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You found that cat here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.99,0:21:29.80,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,He was meowing under there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.01,0:21:32.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bocchan Restaurant is pretty far from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.82,0:21:37.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A cat with two broken legs couldn't \Nhave traveled that distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.06,0:21:38.86,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.11,0:21:39.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.96,0:21:44.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That cat was attacked not at \NBocchan Restaurant, but near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.36,0:21:46.61,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,So, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.60,0:21:51.67,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Edogawa-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bloodstain. What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.92,0:21:56.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That cat's fur is stuck to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.61,0:22:01.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The crime actually took \Nplace here two nights ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.77,0:22:10.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's clear now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.61,0:22:14.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Red Shirt didn't kill Uranari-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.86,0:22:19.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And Red Shirt's suicide was \Nalso a disguised murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.52,0:23:47.89,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's with the weird phrasing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.89,0:23:49.53,DCMain,YAMAARASHI,0000,0000,0000,,You think we did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.73,0:23:52.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the strength of the \Nforce applied to his neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.89,0:23:55.16,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,we believe it was applied by a third party.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.05,0:24:00.91,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A powerful force was applied \Nto his neck? That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.08,0:24:02.92,DCMain,BOCCHAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.37,0:24:07.96,DCMain,NODAIKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way we'd kill the boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.01,0:24:15.01,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Bocchan Restaurant \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.38,0:24:13.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "Welcome \Nto Bocchan Restaurant, Part Two!"
